<kml>

<concept name=Inquire>
<system-documentation name=Inquire>
<superconcept name=Express>

  <definition>
        Expression of a Question.
  </definition>

<requiredslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=object>
       The <slot>agent</slot> expresses <conceptref name=Information> that is a <conceptref name=Question>.
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=agent>
        The <slot>agent</slot> expresses the <conceptref name=Information> in the <slot> object </slot>.
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=recipient>
       the entity that the inquire is expressed to.
  </slotdescription>

</requiredslotlist>

<examplesentencelist>

  <examplesentence>
    <text>Mick inquired to his brother, "Is it raining?".</text>
    <slotdescription name=agent>Mick</slotdescription>
    <slotdescription name=object>"Is it raining?"</slotdescription>
    <slotdescription name=recipient>Mick's brother</slotdescription>
  </examplesentence>

</examplesentencelist>

<neighborlist>
  <neighbor name=Interpret>
	In a <conceptref name=Interpret> the <slot> agent </slot> is the passive receiver of <conceptref name=Information>, but in an Inquire the <slot> agent </slot> is actively expressing the <conceptref name=Information> which is playing the role of a  <conceptref name=Question>. </neighbor>
  <neighbor name=Command>
       	In a <conceptref name=Command> the <conceptref name=Information in the <slot> object </slot> plays the role of <conceptref name=Instruction>, but in an Inquire the information plays the role of a <conceptref name=Question>.
  </neighbor>  

</neighborlist>


</kml>